The latest British opinion poll gaveMargaret Thatcher's Conservative party a huge 17 point leadover the opposition -- the highest rating yet for the primeminister who is seeking a record third consecutive term.    The poll in today's Sun popular tabloid showed theConservatives could win a solid majority of 125 seats inParliament in the next general election.    Thatcher must call an election by June 1988 but is widelyexpected to call it this year.    The survey gave the Conservatives 44 pct of the votes,left-wing Labour and the centrist Liberal-Social DemocraticAlliance 27 pct each. Reuter&#3;